			<ns0:name>pa...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/101628056640429344673/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Currently validator_ragel allows modifying BP and SP via 16bit and 8bit subregs. The test &amp;quot;change-subregs&amp;quot; reveals that. The behavior of validator_ragel maintains all the sandbox invariants (the most significant half of %rbp and %rsp is not modified with these instructions) so it's safe, but it creates a difference with the current validator.

Until these instructions get generated by a common compiler or otherwise impact our users we should make the instructions invalid in validator_ragel. 
